        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Did you use the Portfolio Item Copy app (from your Dashboard OR Reports->Deep Copy Feature) to copy*F43325*for your new Feature? If not, you are missing out on pre-defined, pre-estimated Tasks for Planning, Development, and Testing-- please follow our new Feature Template there! See["
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Feature Status Definitions",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "strong"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "]("
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "https://microstrategy.sharepoint.com/sites/OperatingModel/SitePages/Feature-Readiness-Status-Levels.aspx",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "link",
              "attrs": {
                "href": "https://microstrategy.sharepoint.com/sites/OperatingModel/SitePages/Feature-Readiness-Status-Levels.aspx"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ") for more details! Please delete this text when you've completed the Feature Description.  "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Description",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "strong"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " (In 1-3 sentences, describe the feature, state the personas involved and how this feature solves their problem. A brief overview of why the feature is necessary, what problem it solves, and the benefits it brings to the user or product)"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "In Library, after making changes to report in design mode, one must first save the report to return to consumption mode to export the data. The customer is requesting the ability for users to export reports in Library without having to save the changes first, directly from the editor view. This is a crucial step for any ad-hoc analyst who would build a report, not save it and need to export obtained results for further distribution."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Use Cases",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "strong"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "6. Requirements",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "strong"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "6.1 Business / Technical Requirements",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "strong"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "(Specific functionalities that the feature must include to accomplish the desired tasks. This may include details about data input, system behavior, and data output.)"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "i.e."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "The dossier should be available to selected MicroStrategy employees."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "The prompt and completion tokens should not be available for customers to consume."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "This data is only requested for MCE customers since the AI features will only be available for MCE environments."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "The system should provide the users with the number of requests, number of completion tokens, number of prompt tokens, execution time, and number of users. These metrics should be available at the Day, Time, DSI, License Type, and Feature.  "
                },
                {
                  "type": "hardBreak"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "•    Due to privacy concerns, we should not store the token sent or returned from the LLM.  "
                },
                {
                  "type": "hardBreak"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "•    Every customer using the AI features will purchase a bundle of a certain number of requests (i.e., 20K requests) they will consume each request based on the feature they are using. If they use the generate dossier for the AI canvas feature that will count as a request, if they ask a question to the AI assistant for the Data whisperer, that will count as a request, etc.  "
                },
                {
                  "type": "hardBreak"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "•    [nice-to-have] Start date and expiration date of the AI license key"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "6.2 Cloud Requirements",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "strong"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },

